Overhyped. It’s just okay. I ordered through Ubereats and the fries were cold. Burger was okay but the diced onions reminded me of the diced onions on the cheeseburgers at McDonalds. Shake Shack still reigns as best burger.
VERY NICE AND PROFESSIONAL PEOPLE

An excellent local burger, perhaps the best local burger. Small Cheval lacks nothing in terms of food quality. I'm a portions man though and quantity of food for the high price is lacking. That said, a lunch, dinner, or snack here will not disappoint.

Just better than mc Donald

Delicious.  Best burger in town.  Amazing fries.  My hairstylist that works next door said she only eats the fries cause she's vegetarian, but they're amazing.  I didn't have the heart to tell her they're cooked in beef fat!  French chef's use the best ingredients and it shows!

The 900 N. Michigan location is much better. At the Old Town location, they claim curbside pickup is available, but I've been there twice and each time I had to park, then walk to the back to find the host and get my own food. That's not curbside pickup. It's quite inconvenient especially since all these restaurants are claiming they want and need business yet they make their customers jump through hoops to support them. Oh, and the fries always taste like they were cooked hours ago and kept warm under a light. Hard pass.
Great burgers Great Customer service

good food and polite staff but not good and serving clientele. Ordered online and received an expected time to pickup order. Not only were they 20 minutes late with the order, they make you wait outside in the cold for your food. No curbside and a lot of angry customers when i was there. Not going back
Best burger in Chicago
Great place with good burgers. Outdoor seating and fast service!

It was pretty expensive. The burger got kinda bland and gummy after some time, partly due to them cooking it medium rare without asking. Also, $13.95 for a burger with no lettuce, onions, etc is pretty unexpected. Usually, I have good experiences eating burgers, but sadly, this is not one of them.
Delicious burgers! Loved the aioli.
Good food, but takes forever to get the food
Good burgers and fries
Best burger I have had in a while. Will be going back and bringing friends along.

Ordered for pickup and left the store. Upon arriving home we were short 2 fries and 2 garlic aoilis. No phone number for this location. Tried calling the Milwaukee location and no answer. No way to rectify the issue unless I return to the restaurant which is asinine.  No way to get my money back?  Guess I will call my bank.
Fantastic cheeseburger and fries. Loved the space too.
It looks like is a really well-known place. I liked the food in this place. I saw many people coming to eat here. I courage you all to taste the food.

Order ahead of time.  Decision - to eat heavy burger- or, put it off to when it’s cold outside.  It’s 91 degrees and the service was great—no lines—and, I’m so glad I did!!  So, eat the burger, fries and chocolate shake!  Life is today...eat.
Great place , food and staff !
I always have the best experience at this location. The staff goes above and beyond. I always leave with a smile on my face! Everyone is so friendly and the food is unmatched!!

Generally good food. This time I got there just before 9:20pm they close at 9:30pm. I wanted to place an order for a burger and fry to go. The guy handling orders told me I needed to order online at the website.  I spent five minutes trying to put an order together online when I realized the website was telling me that I could not make an order because there is some unknown time past which the website will not allow you to make an order. I told the guy this And he said he was unaware of this issue. All I wanted was a burger and fry. Shouldn’t be this complicated, very disappointing because the food is good And plenty of others were There picking up orders as I just wanted a burger and fry.

Ok burger. Nothing special. Was expecting way more based on the hype! The patties are not really flavorful and they add to much black pepper on top of them. It’s a kinda burger that you have to add tops to be enjoyable. If you get it plain it’s a big no!

First time trying Small Cheval. For context, I've never had Au Cheval. The service was incredibly pleasant and the servers were helpful. The place was buzzing with business, which is always a good sign.  On to the food: burger was fantastic. You think 2 patties would be too much, but they're thin and the perfect proportion of burger to bun. The pickles also had a nice lemon hint so you can tell they're made in-house. Overall, this is an unpretentious burger that hits the spot. The fries were literally McDonald's fries. Nice and crispy. Weren't astounding, but the aoili made them the perfect dipping vessel.
Amazing burgers. Super convenient and quick to order and enjoy! The burgers are as good as the main restaurant but there are not as much selection in toppings. Still fantastic place to eat
While I wouldn't call this the best burger in Chicago, it's still great.

Great food, easy for pickup and travels well. Very rich, so i don’t recommend doing this for lunch if you have big dinner plans for the day! Otherwise, it’s well worth the wait/cost. Mix their garlic sauce with a bit of ketchup for a 10/10 French fry dipping sauce
Either add a phone number for this location or a message on the website explaining to customers you aren’t taking orders at the store. Otherwise everyone is stuck ordering online when they arrive.
The meat is delicious but the fries are a joke.

My favorite burger !!! I’m from the suburbs but drive all the way here just for their burgers and it is so worth it. A little pricey we pay around $35 for 2 burgers and 2 drinks. It’s not to greasy and taste amazing. Would definitely recommend you try, also seen a lot of people ordering alcoholic drinks.

Ordered for pickup here with three other people, we all basically ordered cheeseburgers and fries. The food was very delicious, as to be expected. It's a flavorful, savory burger that draws from everything that makes a classic burger good while adding it's own unique taste with the dijonnaise.  The wait time for pickup was definitely about 25-30 minutes beyond the estimate, but anyone who has eaten at Small Cheval (or Au Cheval) before should be used to wait times during high demand hours. When we did get our food, you could tell it was fresh off the grill and out the door fast.  A little patience goes a long way; you should expect that they'll be slammed with online delivery orders and may be operating at a reduced capacity. Anyways, with everything else going on, what's the rush? Take a walk around Old Town while you wait and thank the staff for trying their best despite the circumstances.

COVID update: the restaurant shuts down their online ordering periodically throughout the day due to high volume... SUPER annoying but if you can’t order online, try back every 5-10 mins. Wish they had a better process
Waited an extra 32 minutes outside for my order.
Great atmosphere! Great food!
Don't bother to order from this place unless You want to be greeted with an attitude and low service
Takes FOREVER to order and get food on weekends.

By far the tastiest burger I’ve ever had. They keep it super simple with the burgers, fries, and shakes but they absolutely kill it. The fries usually aren’t to my liking unfortunately, mostly overcooked. The burger and the shake is where it’s at. I have yet to try Au Cheval, but considering this place is so close to me with no wait times means I’ll stick to coming here.
Just tried the new location for take and it is just as good as the original! Perfect bun, meat, and cheese. The Mayo/mustard makes this burger perfect.
Loved the cheeseburgers and fries.  The staff makes you feel at home.  In short, small Cheval is a fun spot with great burgers.  Come once, and it'll become a habit; a good one!
Had a great bacon cheeseburger with fries and a chocolate whiskey shake ! Really good
Best burger I've ever had
Nice day, good place to sit outside and have a burger and a beer!

Soooooo good. The burger and the fries but especially the vanilla shake whiskey are soooo good. Went on a week night, around 7:30, crowded but we found a seat. But it’s pretty crazy and loud. If I lived in the neighborhood, I would visit at least once a week for carry-out... maybe everyday for a milkshake which is why it’s a good thing I don’t live nearby!
One of the best burgers I've had In a very long time .....very laid back opened atmosphere..

This burger spot has a fairly small menu, booze and still manages to make a great impression. The burgers are great, well made and the options are not so daunting when you take a look at them. This is a great spot to visit for a bite to eat or even order out, and there is outdoor seating available as well. I would absolutely visit her for the burger and plan on doing so repeatedly, I would recommend the same for anyone looking for a good burger
VERY GOOD!!
A wonderful little oasis of comfort food in Old Town. The food is excellent, the atmosphere, particularly in the summer, is pleasant and cosy, the staff are friendly and welcoming.
This place blows me away everytime I come.  It is not just drunk food...it is good food.  The burgers for some reason just taste different, but in a good delicious way.  Must go.
Best no frills burger around! They keep it simple with strong emphasis on quality. Definitely try out their garlic aioli if you get a chance
Amazing burgers and fries! I love the simple concept

An Old Town staple. As an avid Small Cheval fan, the location specific to my neighborhood is by far my favorite. As it is almost hidden on the street, you have to take a peek into the alley it hides in to see the homey restaurant. The outside seats are perfect for the summer, while the small inside proves comforting during the winter. Food: The fries tend to change from location to location and even timewise at the same Small Cheval location. They are not always as great as they could be, needs consistency. The burgers on the other hand, not gonna say much as I'd advise you to taste them first. There's a uniqueness that brings me back EVERY. SINGLE. TIME.

Happened to find this place on way to the Lincoln Park Zoo and glad we did!! Food was delicious, hot and fresh! The staff were great as well. Super personable, friendly and went above and beyond. Glad we could find this gem. Will definitely be back next time in Chicago.
(Translated by Google) Too good, first time in Chicago and I loved it.  (Original) Demasiado buena, primera vez en Chicago y me encantó.

Best burger I had, not just in Chicago, but probably any restaurant (can’t beat homemade).  The menu is limited, but they do it really well.  There were also plenty of options for condiments. Delicious!

One of the best burgers I’ve had. Be sure to try the garlic aioli dip.

I've heard people say, "It's just like Au Cheval". Let me just go head and set the record straight - it's not.  The burger was just okay; however, they have outdoor seating that's dog friendly, but I could definitely taste the difference between Au Cheval and Small Cheval. The three differences: 1.) You cannot get an egg on top 👎, 2.) The bacon was almost non-existent - absolutely nothing like at Au Cheval, and 3.) They were not cooked to the mouth watering perfection like at Au Cheval. Also, I will add that the price was not that much cheaper than Au Cheval - there was only about a $3 price differential 🙄  To make a long story short, no offense, but I'll be going to Au Cheval next time.

Great small place with a simple setup. The burger is very good, but it’s NOT the same as Au Cheval. However, it’s similar enough and a MUCH better experience. The burgers are smaller and the bacon is what people call “normal” (it’s insanely thick at Au Cheval).  They have everything you need to make the experience though and even the Aioli is on tap ready to roll. Some of best quick service food in the city. Expect to wait 10-15 minutes, but the line moves fast. Seating is mostly outdoor, which makes this an ideal summer spot.  Do it. DO IT. DOO IT.
A nice little hole in a wall place great place to go eat. Food is a little pricey. But that pays with how good the food is. Overall a great place to go eat and talk.

I would like to try new places. But I would not return here. I liked the seats outside and it is a nice place. I did not like the burgers at all, very close to what you get at FiveGuys and perhaps BurgerKing.

Small Cheval is one of our favorites in the neighborhood. Great burgers and amazing milkshakes too!! Don't be intimidated by the line, it usually moves fairly fast and food is served promptly after ordering.

Excellent cheeseburger in a relaxed setting. Meat was cooked medium, basic, yet quality topping. Plenty of condiments for all needs. The fries were thin. They were crisp on the outside and soft on the inside. Lightly salted. Excellent value.

An absolutely amazing burger! Cheesy, greasy, and their garlic aioli...mmmmmm 🤤

There are three things on the menu: burger, cheeseburger, & fries. You can add bacon. It's one of the best menus I've ever seen, for all of it's simplicity. The food was tasty, but if you get fries, eat them quick! They get cold super fast. There are, however, many sauces to choose from (garlic aioli among them, nomnomnom!!!) to help facilitate rapid fry consumption, lol. There are also some alcoholic beverages available, but I can't recall what they were, as I just got a soda. I thought it was cool that they had a few options, though. Maybe I'll get a drink the next time I go, because I will indeed be back, lol. Be aware that the restaurant is quite small and set far back from the street, so it can be easy to miss! Keep your eyes peeled, and look forward to a tasty meal!

good fries.
